**Why SSRF is Particularly Dangerous in Cloud Environments**

  -------------------------------------------------- ----------------------- -----------------------
  **Internal Target**                                **What the Attacker     **Real-World Example**
                                                     Gets**                  

  **http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/**   AWS IAM role            Capital One breach 2019
                                                     credentials --- full    --- \$80M fine, 100M
                                                     account access          records

  **http://localhost:8080/admin**                    Internal admin panel    Many cloud apps expose
                                                     not exposed to internet management APIs on
                                                                             localhost

  **http://192.168.1.1/**                            Router admin interface  Corporate network
                                                     on internal LAN         pivoting after cloud
                                                                             compromise

  **file:///etc/passwd**                             Local server files if   Applicable when fetch
                                                     file:// scheme not      libraries accept
                                                     blocked                 file:// URLs
  -------------------------------------------------- ----------------------- -----------------------

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **SSRF vs SQL Injection --- the same root cause:** in SQLi, the
  attacker\'s input changes the structure of a database query. In SSRF,
  the attacker\'s input changes **where the server makes its next network
  request.** Both are injection variants. The fix principle is identical:
  never trust user input to determine the destination of a privileged
  operation --- whether that operation is a database query or an HTTP
  request.

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
